I will let you know the story of Janmabhoomi SF Exp . Janmabhoomi initially started from VSKP to BZA but later it was extended to Tenali Jn. Those days there is a one more train called Nagarjuna SF Exp  with diesel locomotive from SECUNDRABAD to Tenali Jn. This Nagarjuna exp will start from SC @ 07:00 HRS and will reach Tenali by 12:15  hrs on platform 1 daily and Janmabhoomi SF Exp with Electric locomotive departs VSKP   @ 06:20 hrs and will reach Tenali Jn by 12:30 hrs on platform 2.  Later on people who are from SECUNDRABAD and want to travel to vskp they use to travel by Nagarjuna exp up to TENALI  and board Janmabhoomi exp to vskp. Inthis view South Central decided to remove Nagarjuna SF Exp and wants to extend Janmabhoomi SF Exp up to Secunderabad. That's the final decision by SCR but there is a condition that train has to travel via Tenali because the removed Nagarjuna Exp and extended Janmabhoomi exp both are terminated at Tenali Jn  Positive points for South Central Railway  1. Both Trains are not fully occupied up to tenali because lot of trains are there. But after extention till today entire rake is booked and under waiting list. ............................   Later SCR faces some technical time delay issues with the train leads to complaints from passengers   Reason for delay  Those days SC to TEL JN via GNT  is not electrified route so only diesel Locomotive only can pull the train from Tenali to Secunderabad & Secunderabad to Tenali jn via GNT &  TENALI JN to vskp route is fully electrified so Electrical locomotive will pull the train from Tenali to VSKP.   So here is the picture  The diesel locomotive pull the Janmabhoomi exp from SC to Tenali on Platform 2. The Electric Locomotive will pull Janmabhoomi exp from VSKP to TEL JN on platform 1. There the locomotives will exchange the [ vskp to tenali Janmabhoomi electric locomotive will be attached to Secunderabad to Tenali Janmabhoomi exp and pull up to vskp & the same Secunderabad to Tenali  diesel locomotive will attached to vskp to Tenali Janmabhoomi and pull up to Secunderabad)  Here is the problem when any train either Secunderabad to vskp Janmabhoomi got delay to Tenali then the opposite Janmabhoomi from vskp to Secunderabad has to wait in Tenali jn up to the opposite direction train has yo arrive then Locomotive exchange.    This also leads to so many complaints and finally now SCR Comes with a better plan to avoid delay will let you know on call or if you don't understand u can share ur no to my mail ID so that I can call. My maild : sidhu.lodz@gmail.com

No offence to anyone .  But people reviewing MV KAVARATTI do not know the difference between Cruise and Ship.   A cruise is equivalent to a 5 star hotel . Ones you are inside the ship rarely you will feel a cruise ship is moving at such high speed . There is top notch food , entertainment and service . Yes it is expensive as well.  On the other hand MV Kavaratti is a ship with delux cabins . You will feel the ship moving and people with sea sickness will have problems . These ships are not designed in the same manner a cruise liner is designed hence you will feel the sea turmoil .  If you want to experience Lakshadweep go for this ship but if you want experience a cruise liner then by on means it is a cheaper version of any cruise liner .

Yes. Me and my husband went to Kerala for honeymoon first time to Kerala after marriage. After that we went to house boat trip on our 5th day of trip. For honeymoon couple they will give room decorated with flowers, welcome drink, candle light dinner, and a honeymoon Cake. We stayed overnight in the boat. It was a memorable one. Vemanadu lake lo one side is Aleeppy and other side is kumarakom. You can find boats both sides of lake. Wonderful Experience. Other than going individually or hiring boat individually go with a travel agent with 3nights 4days package it will cost you very cheap. If you go directly house boat it is 12000/-. For 20k you will get whole package with all sightseeing, hotels, all dinners, bus or car to airport or nearest railway station pick up and drop.excluding tickets.
